Yes, the author of this torrent has created a directory in which the longest folder/file path is significant and may give you an error when trying to download.  I had my downloads going to: C:\Documents and Settings\username\My Documents\BitTorrent Downloads\ which created the problem.  This download location path, prepended to the downloaded file path, creates a pathname longer than my system can handle.  The solution:  Move your client's downloads folder to a spot with a short pathname.  I had to save mine to the top-level of my C drive.
